Date: 7/12/1891
Source: Hawke's Bay Herald
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: We should prefer a trial, and if the Burgon Company will agree will meet them at once an arrange details, which shall include the following:- To fit up a shed with an equal number of Burgon and Wolseley machines and cut out the entire flock, and to arrange that the sheep shorn shall include merino and sandy backed sheep; in fact, all classes of sheep - the harder to shear the better the test.
